          {
            "commit": "fc4b46df111bbf9d2207265d18b3f0d72f49502c",
            "subject": "LU-935 quota: break early when b/i_unit_sz exceeded upper limit"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-12-19 10:01:36.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-12-30 02:26:17.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-882 quota: Quota code compares unsigned < 0",
        "message": "LU-882 quota: Quota code compares unsigned < 0\n\nPort from b23858.\n\nIn check_cur_qunit(), it checks \"if (limit + record < 0)\", however,\nthe limit is unsigned, so this check will be always false, and when\nlimit is smaller than -record, following \"limit += record\" will make\nlimit a unreasonable large value.\n\nThis patch also fixed a similar defect in dqacq_handler().\n\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <vladimir.saveliev@oracle.com>\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <niu@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Iea02143dae5542f1a9f9cc823a684a18031b8a03\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
